WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.400 --> 00:00:13.120
Interesting developments
 here at Scotland Yard this morning.

2
00:00:13.560 --> 00:00:17.120
The police case against the notorious
 cyber criminal syndicate

3
00:00:17.120 --> 00:00:19.320
APT is in jeopardy.

4
00:00:19.320 --> 00:00:23.000
Senior Investigating Officer
 Detective Chief Inspector Nicola Crooks

5
00:00:23.160 --> 00:00:26.120
posted on social media last night
 that the majority

6
00:00:26.120 --> 00:00:29.720
of the evidence used against APT
 had been fabricated.

7
00:00:30.080 --> 00:00:33.320
This led to her arrest
 in the early hours of this morning.

8
00:00:33.680 --> 00:00:36.080
Police have declined
 to comment at this stage.

9
00:00:36.520 --> 00:00:39.880
APT were allegedly responsible
 for many cyber attacks

10
00:00:39.880 --> 00:00:43.080
last year against multiple high
 profile targets.

11
00:00:43.280 --> 00:00:46.640
And their case is currently being heard
 at the Old Bailey.

12
00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:49.400
Key evidence is due to be
 heard this afternoon.

13
00:00:49.400 --> 00:00:54.200
So this recent development threatens
 a complete collapse of the prosecution's case.

14
00:00:54.200 --> 00:00:57.560
Defense lawyers  are already demanding
that all proceedings

15
00:00:57.560 --> 00:01:01.360
are dropped immediately
 and DCI Crooks face criminal charges.

16
00:01:01.680 --> 00:01:04.760
For more on this, we go to our crime
 reporter, Ivor Storey.

